fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Please do not do that again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Please do not do that again.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""It looks like the phasmid had some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It looks like the phasmid had some kind of *nest* there -- look. Like a hoard, man..."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, grandpa's not looking so goo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, grandpa's not looking so good. We need to check on him..."

fields.Title: Cuno: "There's a big smile on his lips, li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a big smile on his lips, like he can't believe what he's saying: "We fucking *saw* it, yo -- it was real."

fields.Title: Empathy: "In some kind of strange, semi-catat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In some kind of strange, semi-catatonic state.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "In the reeds, where he's pointing,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the reeds, where he's pointing, you see a flash of white -- *porcelain* white.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "The segmented antennae move with ap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The segmented antennae move with apprehension, searching for something... you.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You smell..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You smell...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "From the corner of your eye, you se..."
fields.Dialogue Text: From the corner of your eye, you see a sudden cascade of motion ripple through the insect's limbs. A series of ultrasonic clicks fills your ear...
fields.Alternate1: From the corner of your eye, you see a sudden cascade of motion ripple through the phasmid's limbs. A series of ultrasonic clicks fills your ear...

fields.Title: Authority: "He's letting his pride get in the w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's letting his pride get in the way.

fields.Title: You: ""You exist...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You exist..."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Meanwhile, in the antechamber of th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Meanwhile, in the antechamber of the Station 57 lazareth, a neatly packed pair of cargo pants and an orange bomber jacket sit in a locker. Nested on the jacket -- a small block of milled aluminium, tucked away in a leather case.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "An instant camera -- the Trigat Sun..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An instant camera -- the Trigat Sunshine Mini. A moan of discomfort sounds from the lazareth, as he turns onto his side...

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Praying to you."
fields.Dialogue Text: Praying to you.

fields.Title: You: "Tell me -- what are you doing?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Tell me -- what are you doing?
fields.tooltip3: Did not give up on phasmid.

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "Kim, it's foaming.""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "Kim, it's foaming."
fields.Alternate1: (Whisper.) "Cuno, it's foaming."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Unwittingly the insect continues it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unwittingly the insect continues its stridulations. As it moves, tuft-like structures still pretending to be plants rustle along on its joints.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The reed-creature does not stop its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The reed-creature does not stop its stridulations -- it towers above you, parting the reeds it emerged from. Tuft like structures still rustle on its joints.

fields.Title: Authority: "About now he is ready to believe in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: About now he is ready to believe in anything.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The paraplegic? She could have, ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The paraplegic? She could have, yes..." He seems unsure.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I never thought the damn *cryptozo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I never thought the damn *cryptozoology* would factor into this... Well, we know it's here now. We *will* find it again."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: ""He must be *really* out of it, yel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He must be *really* out of it, yelling like that. Well, at least he's *alive*...." Officer Minot in the blue uniform frowns: "Jean, maybe something *happened*? He's in distress..."

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""Crypto-what?" Some odd connotation..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Crypto-what?" Some odd connotation catches the old man's ear.

fields.Title: You: "Lick your finger."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lick your finger.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The arthropod towers above you, fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The arthropod towers above you, frozen in place. A twitch passes one of its hind legs, as you...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Feels like nothing. The arthropod i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Feels like nothing. The arthropod in front of you stays frozen...

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Suddenly -- another flash of pain...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Suddenly -- another flash of pain. Worse than the one before. The taste of blood in your mouth. The insect tastes it too, twitching suddenly...

fields.Title: You: "It's *wunderbar*."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's *wunderbar*.
fields.Alternate1: For me it's *wunderbar*.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Shifting around in the reeds around..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shifting around in the reeds around it, in the muddy water... you notice some of its hind legs apparently standing on the water from time to time. It's *that* light...

fields.Title: You: "I'm ill in my head. I'm insane. Tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm ill in my head. I'm insane. That's how it is for me.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "That is your problem. Nothing ever..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That is your problem. Nothing ever ends for me. There is only room for two, maybe three pictures in my mind.

fields.Title: You: "Got it. Solved it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Got it. Solved it.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You are a violent and irrepressible..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You are a violent and irrepressible miracle. The vacuum of cosmos and the stars burning in it are afraid of you. Given enough time you would wipe us all out and replace us with nothing -- just by accident.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "She was middle class. It doesn't ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was middle class. It doesn't take a three-metre stick insect to tell you that.

fields.Title: Half Light: "It may have unknown, dangerous bioc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It may have unknown, dangerous biochemical characteristics that help it maintain its camouflage.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Very slowly -- and only because he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Very slowly -- and only because he won't go away. It is meant to keep them from noticing me, to interfere with the pictures in their heads. But he has looked at me too long. And I'm destroying him.

fields.Title: You: "Of all the creatures I've met you a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of all the creatures I've met you are the scariest.

fields.Title: You: "Okay good. Forget it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay good. Forget it.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Everything your eyes touch goes bac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Everything your eyes touch goes back there -- behind the nerve mirror. What if you blink? Are we still here? (Please don't blink). What if you misplace us all one day -- or just forget?

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Fuck. Where did it go?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck. Where did it go?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""The fuck..." He squints. "Is that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The fuck..." He squints. "Is that *ceramic*? And more stuff -- like a *nest* in the reeds. We should peep it... fucking hell..."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yo, we just saw a giant fucking in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yo, we just saw a giant fucking insect, okay? Focus on that, not some..." He looks around. "Where'd it go?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't understand... I *had* the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't understand... I *had* the pheromone...."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno doesn't know what that means..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno doesn't know what that means -- Cuno just knows it was FUCKING GIANT. Holy hell..."

fields.Title: Authority: "He's truly satisfied with your perf..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's truly satisfied with your performance in Death Island right now.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "No! The flash will scare the creatu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No! The flash will scare the creature off! Warn him NOW!

fields.Title: Half Light: "I am not palatable. Do not eat me...."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am not palatable. Do not eat me. I am afraid.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He comes to, abruptly. "Understood...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He comes to, abruptly. "Understood. Of course," he says with a nod.

fields.Title: You: ""Hey.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The tracheal system on the creature..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tracheal system on the creature's abdomen expands in front of you, to take in and expel air -- it's *smelling* you.

fields.Title: You: "Let your heels drop back onto solid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let your heels drop back onto solid ground.

fields.Title: You: "Put your hand down."
fields.Dialogue Text: Put your hand down.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The invertebrate comes back to life..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The invertebrate comes back to life, stridulating. Sets of complex eyes follow you, moving in tandem, on either side of the insect's small head.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Breathing you in -- your sour, grea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Breathing you in -- your sour, greasy semiochemicals on the breeze...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No..." He shows you the white slip..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No..." He shows you the white slip of photo paper. There's a rainbow of colour -- blue, white, yellow, and brown like a child's painting.

fields.Title: Authority: "Something cracks in the lieutenant...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something cracks in the lieutenant. He's letting his pride get in the way.

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""I don't..." He's extending his han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't..." He's extending his hand into the dust now, for some odd reason. Smearing his finger in it, like a confused child...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "For all time."
fields.Dialogue Text: For all time.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's good, it's good," the lieuten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's good, it's good," the lieutenant whispers, holding it up. "Don't worry. We got it."

fields.Title: Half Light: "It's about to move, you can sense i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's about to move, you can sense it!

fields.Title: You: "I want to know your mind."
fields.Dialogue Text: I want to know your mind.

fields.Title: You: "My body aches. I'm bleeding."
fields.Dialogue Text: My body aches. I'm bleeding.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I smelled it, as soon as you steppe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I smelled it, as soon as you stepped on the island -- strawberries. Fresh burst of red strawberries. Ripe turning riper. Soon you will be rotten.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Fire? Where?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Fire? Where?

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "No -- it's what the three metres ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No -- it's what the three metres tall stick insect came up with.

fields.Title: You: "*How?*"
fields.Dialogue Text: *How?*

fields.Title: You: "So you look like a reed, and you ea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So you look like a reed, and you eat reeds?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "*I* think we should eat it. If it's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *I* think we should eat it. If it's a leaf you can put it in your mouth. Or a reed. Yum yum.

fields.Title: You: "Also that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Also that.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. What's going on?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. What's going on?"

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Nothing but you, a detective of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing but you, a detective of the RCM, standing there with your mouth agape.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, how do you know about the ph..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, how do you know about the phasmid?"
fields.Alternate1: "Wait -- Insulindian Phasmid? How do you know this?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [Insulindian Phasmid: "The insect's head is crowned with r..."]
Inland Empire: "Be afraid. You smell wrong."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be afraid. You smell wrong.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, take the picture.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, take the picture."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The ghost insect watches you diseng..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The ghost insect watches you disengage, continuing its hypnotizing motion. It's unclear whether it even registers that you're going...

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "A camera -- an instant colour camer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A camera -- an instant colour camera the lieutenant keeps tucked away in his coat pocket. A moan of discomfort sounds from the lazareth, as he turns onto his side...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No reply. A total, ancient silence..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No reply. A total, ancient silence comes from its mouth, along with what appears to be some kind of foam... The stridulations of its limbs continue all around you.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Our suspect's not looking so good...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our suspect's not looking so good. We should check him over -- also..." He points to the reeds.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Helped them?" He falls silent for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Helped them?" He falls silent for a moment. "I don't see what more we could have done?"

fields.Title: You: ""I should have taken the pheromone!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should have taken the pheromone!"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["coast.morells_pheromone_spray"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid_done"] == false  and  Variable["coast.morell_refused_ox_spray"] == true

fields.Title: You: ""Lieutenant, it's thinking with its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lieutenant, it's thinking with its *limbs*."

fields.Title: You: "(I'm sure.) "We got it, Kim..." (Ke..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (I'm sure.) "We got it, Kim..." (Keep backing.)

fields.Title: You: "In my heart. For me it's sadness --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In my heart. For me it's sadness -- input after input.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I am not. There isn't even a centra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am not. There isn't even a central nervous system in my head. Only mouthparts for eating wetland plants.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. The leg tried to move around in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. The leg tried to move around independently, making it hard to walk.

fields.Title: You: "No, I'm not. Why are you asking?"
fields.Dialogue Text: No, I'm not. Why are you asking?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The leg tried to move around indepe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The leg tried to move around independently, making it hard to walk.

fields.Title: You: "...how?"
fields.Dialogue Text: ...how?

fields.Title: You: ""Okay good. Forget it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay good. Forget it."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Good bye. A series of chirrups surr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good bye. A series of chirrups surrounds you, like swallows on a cliff side, as the phasmid moves its forearms -- tymbals visible on the inside of its white stalks...

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "...and something under it! In the p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...and something under it! In the place it stood, bobbing there, among the reeds. A collection of items.

fields.Title: You: "Am I having a violent epileptic sei..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Am I having a violent epileptic seizure?

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["seafort.phasmid_branch_insane_miracle"] == true  and  IsCunoInParty() == false  and  IsKimHere() == false

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Please be. Or one day one of you wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Please be. Or one day one of you will close your eyes and sigh -- and open them to see that none of this ever existed.

fields.Title: Logic: "Oh my god, *Kim* had the camera!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh my god, *Kim* had the camera!

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Doesn't look like you're spazzin'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't look like you're spazzin' out" he whispers behind you. "Cuno knows all about seizures."

fields.Title: You: ""What does it look like?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What does it look like?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""You're just staring at the giant i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're just staring at the giant insect."

fields.Title: You: ""It can walk on water.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It can walk on water."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Our suspect is not looking so good..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our suspect is not looking so good. We need to check on him -- also..." He points to the reeds.

fields.Title: You: ""I shouldn't have taken a bath, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I shouldn't have taken a bath, the pheromone washed off!"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Between the reeds there -- it does..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Between the reeds there -- it doesn't like bein' out in the open. Shifty fuck... I saw it slip in there. It's gone now, but..." He pants. "Wow."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Relax. Now that you *know* it's her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Relax. Now that you *know* it's here -- how long can it hide?

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Sssss-hsssss-tik-ssssss-hssss-tik....."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sssss-hsssss-tik-ssssss-hssss-tik...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We need a photo -- or no one will..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We need a photo -- or no one will believe us." He continues to pull the lens open...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Back on an island 28 kilometres awa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Back on an island 28 kilometres away, the gigantic insect moves its antennae, taking its measure of the air, slowly... it's searching for something -- *you*.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "You barely get to take one step --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You barely get to take one step -- the invertebrate reacts with uncanny speed, skating away across the water. It's gone, like a skipping stone, leaving nothing but rings on the sea's calm mirror...

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper) "Okay Kim, take the pictu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper) "Okay Kim, take the picture."
fields.Alternate1: (Whisper.) "Kim, show me the picture again..."

fields.Title: You: "Put your hands down instead."
fields.Dialogue Text: Put your hands down instead.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay..." With a slow ring of metal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay..." With a slow ring of metal, the lieutenant slides the lens open and raises it to eye level.

fields.Title: You: ""It *did* have something to do with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It *did* have something to do with the ox-spray!"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Even a wildlife photographer couldn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even a wildlife photographer couldn't make out a familiar form, let alone a gigantic stick insect.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "There's a flicker of a smile on his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a flicker of a smile on his lips, like he can't believe what he's saying: "We *saw* it -- it was real."

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What now..." the old man behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now..." the old man behind you repeats suddenly. He's put his hand into the ash -- it's dirty and black.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It looks like it has some kind of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It looks like it has some kind of nest there... Maybe there's proof in there."

fields.Title: You: ""God, I shouldn't have taken a bath..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "God, I shouldn't have taken a bath! The pheromone washed off!"

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "A sudden shiver passes the limb. Lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A sudden shiver passes the limb. Looks like the creature is awakening, wave by wave from its stupor.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Not even the birds know that. Not e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not even the birds know that. Not even the water lilies.

fields.Title: You: "Is this a dream? What is happening?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Is this a dream? What is happening?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "For me it is not like that. I have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For me it is not like that. I have states, not emotions. For example, I experience excitement at unexpected sugar rewards, but that is not important.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. You are the miracle."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. You are the miracle.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "ARRIVING"
fields.Dialogue Text: ARRIVING

fields.Title: You: "The killer."
fields.Dialogue Text: The killer.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "She was hell on Earth. It doesn't t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was hell on Earth. It doesn't take a three-metre stick insect to tell you that.

fields.Title: You: "I have already forgotten the whole..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have already forgotten the whole world once -- when I drank too much.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Everybody does. It's the fucking I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Everybody does. It's the fucking Insulindian phasmid."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay good. Forget it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay good. Forget it."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""It's gone..." Cuno stares to the n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's gone..." Cuno stares to the north. "Between those reeds there. Fucking hell it can..."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Now that you know it exists -- you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now that you know it exists -- you can get it another day. It can't hide forever...

fields.Title: Cuno: ""It looks like the insect had some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It looks like the insect had some kind of *nest* there -- look. Like a hoard, or some shit..."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "No! The flash will scare the creatu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No! The flash will scare the creature. Warn him NOW!

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "He not as much as glances at the gi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He not as much as glances at the gigantic insect to his right -- nor does it look at him. Its antennae take their measure of the air, slowly... searching for something -- *you*.

fields.Title: You: "(Look up.) "You're smelling me...""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Look up.) "You're smelling me..."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["seafort.phasmid_ency_smelling_you"] == true  and  IsKimHere() == false  and  IsCunoInParty() == false

fields.Title: You: ""What now?" (Continue.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now?" (Continue.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's just a blur," he says, lookin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's just a blur," he says, looking at the slip of paper in his hand.

fields.Title: You: "(Yell.) "No!""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Yell.) "No!"

fields.Title: You: ""No one will believe me... no one w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No one will believe me... no one will believe this was real."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You were right, it glistens with so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You were right, it glistens with some kind of moisture. The creature in front of you stays frozen...

fields.Title: You: "I want there to be more."
fields.Dialogue Text: I want there to be more.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Mute, the insect foams from its mou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Mute, the insect foams from its mouthparts, tilting the plates of its fused together head. From left to right, without reason.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I exist."
fields.Dialogue Text: I exist.
fields.Alternate1: I exist.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Something stirs in the insect as yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something stirs in the insect as you begin to back off. It seems to also takes a step back... Something tells you -- the next time you engage and disengage it will probably flee.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. You are awake. I am real. Light..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. You are awake. I am real. Light is forming me. This is real.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Shapes of plants and animals. And *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shapes of plants and animals. And *internal* sensations. A swarm of sounds, tiny vibrations on the inside of my forearms -- all speak of complexities totally beyond my understanding.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Now I will tell you how it is for m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now I will tell you how it is for me. For me it is a series of half-lit images. A kind of darkness, being intruded upon. Transient. Dim. Moist.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Sometimes, when moulting, I regrow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sometimes, when moulting, I regrow a lost limb. One time something went wrong and a small leg replaced a missing antenna.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. They don't mind."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. They don't mind.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No one believed I exist -- almost n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one believed I exist -- almost no one. Until you came, detective. Dripping of blood that smells like strawberries. Across the calm sea, the first in a thousand years.

fields.Title: You: ""I think I'm having a vision. About..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think I'm having a vision. About the final fate of mankind."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "And just like that it's gone -- ska..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And just like that it's gone -- skating away across the sea's calm mirror like a skipping stone, leaving nothing but  circles on the water...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I already did."
fields.Dialogue Text: I already did.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "What if it's not you? What if the t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if it's not you? What if the three metres tall stick insect is having the vision -- while you're alone and  petrified.

fields.Title: You: "I don't want to know."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't want to know.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "So it is *already* happening. One d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So it is *already* happening. One day, one of you will close your eyes and sigh -- and open them to see that none of this ever existed.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Whoah... maybe it's poison? Fuckin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whoah... maybe it's poison? Fucking hell..." The kid watches you apprehensively.

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno. Am I having a violent epilep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno. Am I having a violent epileptic seizure?"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""No, quit frontin'. What's up with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, quit frontin'. What's up with you? We're a team, cop."

fields.Title: You: ""I think I'm having a vision. About..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think I'm having a vision. About the final fate of mankind."

fields.Title: You: ""What now?" [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now?" [Leave.]

fields.Title: Empathy: "In some kind of strange, semi-catat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In some kind of strange, semi-catatonic state. He's not looking so good.

fields.Title: Cuno: "Your voice echoes alone on the wate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice echoes alone on the water. The kid looks at you...

fields.Title: You: ""What in the name of *god* was that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What in the name of *god* was that?"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "And you'll see it again. Now that y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And you'll see it again. Now that you *know* it's real, how long can it hide?

fields.Title: You: ""I should have taken the pheromone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should have taken the pheromone from Morell!"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["coast.morells_pheromone_spray"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid_done"] == true  and  Variable["coast.morell_refused_ox_spray"] == true

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""My camera.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "My camera."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I won't be one of those fools who..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I won't be one of those fools who didn't take a picture..." He has stopped fiddling with the camera, but does not put it down.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "A sudden chirrup fills the air -- t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A sudden chirrup fills the air -- the walking stick moves its whole body, limbs working independently of each other, like the parts of a masterfully constructed machine.

fields.Title: Empathy: "There is a sadness in there -- or i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is a sadness in there -- or is it in you, from the dream... It's still with you, the pitiful *hey* you told her, even now...

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "That's right. Pray.""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "That's right. Pray."

fields.Title: You: "(Yell.) "No!""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Yell.) "No!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "In some kind of strange, semi-catat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In some kind of strange, semi-catatonic state.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I know. We *should* have... It's m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know. We *should* have... It's my fault too." He looks across the water. The slip of photo paper still drying in his hand, just hanging there for a second.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Reed-like tufts stick out of its jo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reed-like tufts stick out of its joints. As the insect moves its forearms it produces a faint hiss -- like a reel-to-reel machine spinning after the tape breaks.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Where? Where did it go?" The lieut..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where? Where did it go?" The lieutenant has the camera in one hand -- and a slip of white paper in the other, developing.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The ampoule will produce a loud hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The ampoule will produce a loud hiss." He turns to you and whispers: "You're right. It could scare it away. I need a better moment, when it's not looking."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Or a *ryacintha*, an Occidental lea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Or a *ryacintha*, an Occidental leaf insect with its brain stored in four leaf-like extensions. Or a mimicry octopus with its intelligent tentacles...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "For me it is a series of half-lit i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For me it is a series of half-lit images. A kind of darkness, being intruded upon. Transient. Dim. Moist.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Change of topic!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Change of topic!

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I am an unknown species of the orde..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am an unknown species of the order Phantasmodea -- endemic to the Insulindian isola. For the last three hundred and fifty years I have hidden in plain sight, masquerading as the reeds. Moulding, cloning myself, unfolding at night to play with trash bins and buoys.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I went unnoticed by the first settl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I went unnoticed by the first settlers and the land surveyors of the suzerain. Also by the soldiers of the Revolution and the officials of the occupation. Even the Semenese islanders who came here first, but did not stay, have not seen me.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. *You* are. The moral of our enc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. *You* are. The moral of our encounter is: I am a relatively median lifeform -- while it is you who are total, extreme madness. A volatile simian nervous system, ominously new to the planet.

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing. Just looking at the stick..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing. Just looking at the stick insect. Everything is normal."

fields.Title: You: "What does it look like?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What does it look like?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Hissing and clicking, the arthropod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hissing and clicking, the arthropod extends its mandible-like antennae to greet you again. You're right below it, looking up at the colossal chitin of its white limbs. Its small eyes look at nothing in particular.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You never had a chance. There was s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You never had a chance. There was something off the moment you approached it... The creature didn't *like* you.

fields.Title: You: ""What's that, in the water?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's that, in the water?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "In some kind of strange, semi-catat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In some kind of strange, semi-catatonic state.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "The air moves through it. Its slend..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air moves through it. Its slender sticks.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We *need* a photo -- no one will b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We *need* a photo -- no one will believe us." He continues to pull the lens open...

fields.Title: You: ""Stop. Let me approach it first.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Stop. Let me approach it first."
fields.Alternate1: "It's afraid. Stop *now*."

fields.Title: The Deserter: "No one hears you whisper. Behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one hears you whisper. Behind you, the straggler sits despondently by the fire, oblivious to his surroundings.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "There is no change in the insects m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is no change in the insects motion while its being aimed by the camera. It remains fixated on you.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Neither have you. But you know who..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Neither have you. But you know who would -- a cryptozoologist!

fields.Title: You: ""What in the name of god was that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What in the name of god was that?"

fields.Title: You: ""I should have helped the cryptozoo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should have helped the cryptozoologists. It's too late now..."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["coast.morells_pheromone_spray"] == false  and  Variable["tc.insulindian_phasmid"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid_done"] == false

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there was one...

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Three-hundred metres inland special..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Three-hundred metres inland special consultant Trant Heidelstam cups his ear. Satellite-Officer Vicquemare nods to him on the jetty: "I heard it."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "A small shudder passes the creature..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A small shudder passes the creature's arm. High above you its black pearl-eyes still glisten, mesmerized by the light passing its nervous system.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "It is impossible to see inside. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is impossible to see inside. There is only chitin, pretending to be reeds -- or polished, like stalks of marble. The occasional series of clicks, undecipherable to the human ear.

fields.Title: You: "Not now..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not now...

fields.Title: You: "Intruded upon -- by what?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Intruded upon -- by what?

fields.Title: You: "This is my masterpiece."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is my masterpiece.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "And when you fall we will come to r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And when you fall we will come to raise you up, bud from you, banner-like, blossom from you and carry you apart in a sky funeral. In honour of your passing. (But not me, because I am just a leaf eater.)

fields.Title: Volition: "In honour of your will, lieutenant-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In honour of your will, lieutenant-yefreitor. That you kept from falling apart, in the face of sheer terror. Day after day. Second by second.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You can also eat it. If it's a leaf..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can also eat it. If it's a leaf you can put it in your mouth. Yum yum. Or a reed.

fields.Title: You: "No. This is just an accident."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. This is just an accident.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I think we should take the picture..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think we should take the picture -- and then you should *back away* from the unstudied species."

fields.Title: You: "I will."
fields.Dialogue Text: I will.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No." You have rarely seen him with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No." You have rarely seen him with that face.

fields.Title: You: "Have you accidentally eaten another..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Have you accidentally eaten another reed-phasmid?

fields.Title: Cuno: ""This is so sick. It *likes* you......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is so sick. It *likes* you..." The kid's mouth is agape.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Like a water spider, or like -- on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like a water spider, or like -- one of those water walkers..." He's lost for words, just pants from excitement. "This cop shit is *insane*"

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "In the reeds, where the phasmid was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the reeds, where the phasmid was hiding, you see a little flash of white -- *porcelain* white.

fields.Title: You: ""I should have taken the pheromone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should have taken the pheromone from Morell!"

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["coast.morells_pheromone_spray"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.find_phasmid_done"] == false  and  Variable["coast.morell_refused_ox_spray"] == true

fields.Title: You: ""I could have learned something abo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I could have learned something about the phasmid's behaviour. Searched for it with them."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there was one...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The creature stands on long stilt-l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The creature stands on long stilt-like legs, antennae hanging from its head like a woman's hair -- white and curled at the tips. It is no more than five steps away from you.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Nothing changes in the cyclical, pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing changes in the cyclical, praying motion of the creature's limbs. They are porcelain white on the inside, and reed-coloured on the out -- beige, light brown and striped. You are unsure if it is scared or not.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The foam slowly turns a darker shad..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The foam slowly turns a darker shade, like burnt caramel -- as the insect moves its mouthparts, masticating. The little bubbles begin to burst, one by one...

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "Letting out that same smell, like s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Letting out that same smell, like summer burning.

fields.Title: You: ""Don't pray to me. I'm nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't pray to me. I'm nothing."

fields.Title: You: ""I shouldn't have taken a bath, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I shouldn't have taken a bath, the pheromone washed off!"

fields.Title: You: ""You didn't get the picture?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You didn't get the picture?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "It's too late now."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's too late now.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You see the insect turn to him, its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see the insect turn to him, its mandible antennae reaching out. Its motions are quick, sudden.
fields.Alternate1: You see the phasmid turn to him, its mandible antennae reaching out. The motions are quick, sudden.

fields.Title: You: "It's not use telling him..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not use telling him...

fields.Title: You: "Carefully pet its scythe-like forea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Carefully pet its scythe-like forearm.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Here, within the smooth white inner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Here, within the smooth white inner part of its limb you sense... something very intimate. Thoughts.

fields.Title: You: "It's your secret alone."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's your secret alone.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Another shudder pulses through the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another shudder pulses through the creatures limbs. It jolts back to life, like a record continuing were it left off -- in a swaying, praying motion. Even the small black pearls of its eyes do not stray from you...

fields.Title: Half Light: "For a moment there, he was afraid y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For a moment there, he was afraid you didn't *get it*, but he's calmer now, looking at it.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A nest?" The whisper is anxious. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A nest?" The whisper is anxious. "Don't do anything now. Later, when it's gone maybe..."

fields.Title: You: "In the city, all around. It's going..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the city, all around. It's going *down*.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Of course, it is nothing compared t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course, it is nothing compared to the horror that is you -- with all of creation reflected in your forebrain, in terrible fidelity, a fire mirror. Eternal, never-ending damnation.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim. Am I having a violent epilept..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim. Am I having a violent epileptic seizure?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay." After a second the lieutena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay." After a second the lieutenant asks: "Is it somehow related to the case?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Maybe you would find it interesting..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe you would find it interesting!

fields.Title: You: "That's insane."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's insane.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's gone..." The lieutenant looks..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's gone..." The lieutenant looks north, with his hand raised to his brow.
fields.Alternate1: "It's gone..." The lieutenant looks north, with the camera uselessly hanging from his fingers.

fields.Title: Authority: "Nothing but you, a detective of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing but you, a detective of the RCM, standing there with your mouth agape.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Looks like material for some kind o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like material for some kind of nest. You should search it.

fields.Title: Empathy: "He is *very* disappointed you didn'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is *very* disappointed you didn't warn him -- or plan it with him...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "We suspect it will be something lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We suspect it will be something like the oxygen holocaust that wiped out anaerobic life 2.6 billion years ago -- when organisms first started breathing. Only much worse.

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno... there's something there.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno... there's something there."

fields.Title: Volition: "He's right. Dust yourself off and m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's right. Dust yourself off and move on. There will be other chances.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Like laughter. A sort of happiness."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like laughter. A sort of happiness.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Silence. Click. The foam slowly tur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Silence. Click. The foam slowly turns a darker tone, like burnt caramel -- as the insect moves its mouthparts, masticating on nothing in particular. Then the little bubbles begin to burst, one by one...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The invertebrate stops, raising its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The invertebrate stops, raising its scythe-like arms and tilting its tiny head, formed from the fused plates around its mouth. For a second, the effigy is frozen, then it nudges back into motion with a click.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The shrill flash of the camera cuts..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The shrill flash of the camera cuts the air like the blade of a sword. The phasmid freezes in its bright light -- head turned toward the lieutenant. Hypnotized by the flash, it stands frozen before you.

fields.Title: Shivers: "The sweat on your arms feels cold a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sweat on your arms feels cold as ice. As if you're frozen as well, in the shadow of this giant statue of chitinous marble.

fields.Title: Half Light: "It *definitely* had something to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It *definitely* had something to do with the ox-spray! It was repelled by you, as if it was scared.

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What was what?" The straggler look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What was what?" The straggler looks around. "It's just the reeds, playing tricks on you, droite..."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Warning!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Warning!

fields.Title: You: "Wipe it off."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wipe it off.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Officially, it was the three metres..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Officially, it was the three metres tall stick insect who solved it.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "So, you see, it's sometimes difficu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So, you see, it's sometimes difficult to be an insect. All of nature is a kind of horror, or strife -- though none of it as horrible as you. With all of creation reflected in your forebrain.

fields.Title: You: "I was born to detect you."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was born to detect you.

fields.Title: You: "That's absolutely nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's absolutely nothing.

fields.Title: Authority: "ON THE SCENE"
fields.Dialogue Text: ON THE SCENE

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "He is in a bad state, deteriorating..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is in a bad state, deteriorating fast now. He thinks I am beneficial to him, but I am not. I only quicken his deterioration.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "She was hell on Earth. It doesn't t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was hell on Earth. It doesn't take a three-metre stick insect to tell you that.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "It doesn't look like that."
fields.Dialogue Text: It doesn't look like that.

fields.Title: You: "Then, I think I'm having a vision...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then, I think I'm having a vision. About the final fate of mankind.

fields.Title: You: "Okay. Just looking at the stick ins..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay. Just looking at the stick insect. Everything is normal.

fields.Title: Logic: "The Deserter, he's been here for a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The Deserter, he's been here for a *long* time.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, what is the pale?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, what is the pale?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Also very, very dangerous."
fields.Dialogue Text: Also very, very dangerous.

fields.Title: You: ""God, Kim had a camera. Do you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "God, Kim had a camera. Do you?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [Esprit de Corps: "Meanwhile, in the antechamber of th..."]
Esprit de Corps: "Meanwhile, in the antechamber of th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Meanwhile, in the antechamber of the Station 57 lazareth, a neatly packed pair of cargo pants and a black bomber jacket sit in a locker. Nested on the jacket -- a small block of milled aluminium, tucked away in a leather case.

fields.Title: You: "Blink. (Quick.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: Blink. (Quick.)

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. For me everything is *always*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. For me everything is *always* normal. God is in his heaven -- everything is normal on Earth.

fields.Title: Empathy: "In some kind of strange, semi-catat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In some kind of strange, semi-catatonic state.

fields.Title: You: ""I think it went into the reeds the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it went into the reeds there, on that islet..." (Point North.)

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, I didn't know it would be *c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, I didn't know it would be *connected* to the case..."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Man, quit beatin' yourself down, w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Man, quit beatin' yourself down, we just discovered a GIANT INSECT. Ain't no one done that..." He looks across the water.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. It was GIANT.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. It was GIANT."

fields.Title: You: "Approach carefully."
fields.Dialogue Text: Approach carefully.
fields.tooltip5: Your corpse will be marked by stars
fields.tooltip6: The miracle, way out in the west

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "The faintest smell, like you've nev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The faintest smell, like you've never felt before. Like burnt roses.

fields.Title: Volition: "Subdue the regret. Dust yourself of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Subdue the regret. Dust yourself off, proceed. You'll get it in the next life, where you don't make mistakes. Do what you can with this one, while you're alive.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: ""He must be *really* out of it, yel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He must be *really* out of it, yelling like that. Well, at least he's *alive*...." Officer Minot in the blue uniform frowns: "Jean, maybe something *happened*? He's in distress..."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Three-hundred metres inland, on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Three-hundred metres inland, on the jetty, special consultant Trant Heidelstam cups his ear. Satellite-Officer Vicquemare nods to him: "I heard it."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The nervous system could be spread..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The nervous system could be spread out like that..." He whispers behind you. "Over the extremities, like a cuttlefish."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Some sort of countdown process is h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Some sort of countdown process is happening. That's all you have time to think...

fields.Title: Suggestion: "They are filled with adoration and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They are filled with adoration and curiosity. The adoration of some wheel,  or dominion spinning around its parent deity. And the curiosity of a common wasp, tasting sugar in a fizzy drink.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "It's spread too thin among its limb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's spread too thin among its limbs, performing incomprehensible operations on the world; and you -- looking at it, mouth slightly open... You cannot even imagine what it thinks.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Another flash of pain. Again you sw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another flash of pain. Again you swallow it, but this time, some of it does not stay down. You think you taste it in your mouth. So does the insect, twitching suddenly...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "As you're turning away, the phasmid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you're turning away, the phasmid mirrors your movements, stepping on the water -- the long limbs carry its feather weight without breaking its surface.

fields.Title: You: "You're the type of animal I would l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're the type of animal I would like to be.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "This would explain its antenna bein..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This would explain its antenna being smaller.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You want to be a phasmid? Are you s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You want to be a phasmid? Are you sure?

fields.Title: You: ""The case? The case is meaningless..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The case? The case is meaningless compared to this." (Laugh nervously.) "I have totally transcended the case."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Wait, so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, so...

fields.Title: You: "I don't have that kind of power."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't have that kind of power.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I think you should back away from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think you should back away from the unstudied species now..."

fields.Title: You: "This is the Gloaming I've been wait..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is the Gloaming I've been waiting for. Ever since I woke up in the hotel room.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Wait, we have to do something!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, we have to do something!"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno doesn't know anything about i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno doesn't know anything about it, though. Except you stink bad, which is why it left you."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: ""He must be *really* out of it, yel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He must be *really* out of it, yelling like that. Well, at least he's *alive*...." Officer Minot in the blue uniform frowns: "Jean, maybe something *happened*? He's in distress..."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, yes, you're probably right...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, yes, you're probably right. I won't panic."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Looks like camera! Yes!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like camera! Yes!

fields.Title: You: ""Just listen to me!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just listen to me!"

fields.Title: You: ""Don't be afraid...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be afraid..."

fields.Title: You: ""I should have taken the pheromone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should have taken the pheromone from Morell!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I tried," he explains. "But it was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I tried," he explains. "But it was moving too fast. And I didn't get the ampoule in right. And..." He gathers himself. "Dammit. I believe my eyes. It *was* there."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The paraplegic? *Or* the other one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The paraplegic? *Or* the other one on the coast? They could have, yes..." He seems unsure.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Like a junkie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a junkie...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "It is surprisingly delicate -- the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is surprisingly delicate -- the curly end of the whisker, like a young bine. It's even a bit wet.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "There is some kind of countdown hap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is some kind of countdown happening, as it slowly processes the overwhelming brightness of the signal. The invertebrate is regaining control...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Another shudder passes through the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another shudder passes through the forearm under your palm -- feels like blood pumping through a brain. It's coming to, you withdraw your hand slowly.

fields.Title: You: "No, wait..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, wait...

fields.Title: You: "Fire, burning."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fire, burning.
fields.Alternate1: For me, it's fire, burning.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "And... is that a glimmer in the wat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And... is that a glimmer in the water, below it? Like plastic? Could it be hoarding something?

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Of course, no time. The insect towe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course, no time. The insect towers above you, parting the reeds it emerged from.

fields.Title: You: "Inside."
fields.Dialogue Text: Inside.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I am oblivious to the city. It is o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am oblivious to the city. It is only on my margins. A ball I sometimes spin. A toy, Or the cylinder of a discarded trash bin.

fields.Title: You: "*This* is the explanation I came up..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *This* is the explanation I came up with?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The moral of our encounter is: I am..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The moral of our encounter is: I am a relatively median lifeform, while you are extreme, all-engulfing madness. A volatile simian nervous system, ominously new to the planet.

fields.Title: You: "See! It's nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: See! It's nothing.

fields.Title: You: "I have to say good bye now. I have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have to say good bye now. I have no more thoughts. That was all.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. No one believed I exist -- almo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. No one believed I exist -- almost no one. Until you came, detective. Dripping of blood that smells like strawberries.  Across the calm sea, the first in a thousand years.

fields.Title: You: "Are you poisonous?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Are you poisonous?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I can also detect pheromones -- the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I can also detect pheromones -- the ones on you tell me that you will not eat me. And that I will benefit from your closeness. In short, I love you.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "It was you. Coming from the west. F..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was you. Coming from the west. From the Whirling. You were coming...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The arthropod follows you with its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The arthropod follows you with its antennae. As you back off, the cracks and hisses of the tape that's come to its end grow more distant...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "It is a nervous shadow cast into th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is a nervous shadow cast into the world by you, eating away at reality. A great, unnatural territory. Its advent coincides with the arrival of the human mind.

fields.Title: You: "Worse how?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Worse how?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "So it is already happening. Soon, o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So it is already happening. Soon, one of you will close your eyes -- and open them to see that none of this ever existed.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "I'll wait. I'm on standby, he think..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'll wait. I'm on standby, he thinks, his hands sweaty around the machine.

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What now..." the old man behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now..." the old man behind you says suddenly. He's put his hand into the ash -- it's dirty and black.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "We'll find it again, man. We'll get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We'll find it again, man. We'll get it, junior officer Cuno thinks. We'll fuckin' nail that phasmid one day.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Its insect mind is impenetrable to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Its insect mind is impenetrable to your reasoning.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It appears the insect can walk on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It appears the insect can walk on water. Like a water strider, you know. It's almost as fast..." He stops, short of breath. "Uncanny..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Your voice echoes on the water."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice echoes on the water.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like it doesn't like to stay..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like it doesn't like to stay out in the open for long." The lieutenant squints where you're pointing.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right."

fields.Title: You: ""Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it right..." [Leave in rage.]

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, yes, you're probably right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, yes, you're probably right."

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "What more is there in any of us? Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What more is there in any of us? You think, as the sight of the insect fades and pain shoots up your right foot and into your abdomen, darkening your view... when it returns the insect twitches, feeling the blood on you...

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "In its marrow -- a combination of c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In its marrow -- a combination of complex biomolecules. Hormones, amino acids, lipids.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I don't know. You're just a shadow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know. You're just a shadow for me. Far away, faintly transmitting, but for a curious smell.

fields.Title: You: "All's well that ends well."
fields.Dialogue Text: All's well that ends well.

fields.Title: You: "Yes I'm sure. Why do you ask?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes I'm sure. Why do you ask?

fields.Title: You: ""Then, I think I'm having a vision...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then, I think I'm having a vision. About the final fate of mankind."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You're just staring at it," he whi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're just staring at it," he whispers.

fields.Title: You: "Then all we can do is beat our fist..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then all we can do is beat our fists against it? Day after day. With no answer.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The creature appears to have forgiv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The creature appears to have forgiven your nerves -- for now. There it still stands, a thin ghost on stilt-like legs. Antennae hang from its head, like curled strands of human hair.

fields.Title: You: "I will try."
fields.Dialogue Text: I will try.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""...the Insulindian phasmid," he fi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...the Insulindian phasmid," he finishes your sentence in awe.
fields.Alternate1: "The Insulindian phasmid," he says with his voice lowered in awe.

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What now..." the old man behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now..." the old man behind you repeats suddenly. He withdraws his hand from the ash -- it's dirty and black.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Damn... Cuno's read about that shi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn... Cuno's read about that shit in a *book*. Cuno's booked that shit. That was, like, a secret animal. Like one of those they *think* is real but haven't seen. The Insulindian phasmid..."

fields.Title: You: ""Who's gonna believe this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who's gonna believe this?"

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What now..." the old man behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now..." the old man behind you says suddenly. He's put his hand into the ash -- it's dirty and black.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You were right. Little bubbles form..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You were right. Little bubbles form on the mouthparts of the creature -- on its segmented lower lip. It looks to be foaming, slowly. The foam is white, then yellowish...

fields.Title: You: ""Why are you're foaming?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you're foaming?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A stick insect of some sort. Prete..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A stick insect of some sort. Pretending to be the reeds..." He shakes his head. "Has it been there the whole time?"

fields.Title: Suggestion: "You never had a chance. There was s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You never had a chance. There was something off the moment you approached it. It was scared of you. Of humans.

fields.Title: You: ""It was *definitely* that. He didn'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was *definitely* that. He didn't like me. I didn't get to take a single step."

fields.Title: Composure: "Like a little boy... for a moment h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a little boy... for a moment he's unable to keep it together when he looks at the slip.

fields.Title: The Deserter: "Looks like you're right. He's exten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like you're right. He's extending his hand into the dust now, for some odd reason. Smearing his finger in it, confused like a child...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The antennae hang from a great heig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The antennae hang from a great height. With your hand shaking you barely touch the tip of the left whisker. On contact the chitin curls into a spiral, like the tip of a poison ivy. Its touch on your fingertip feels cold, ticklish...

fields.Title: Perception (Taste): "Odourless, mostly comprised of wate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Odourless, mostly comprised of water.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Now I will tell you what it's like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now I will tell you what it's like for me. For me it is a series of half-lit images. A kind of darkness, being intruded upon. Transient. Dim. Moist.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "What is your illness?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What is your illness?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes, holy is the lord of hosts. And..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, holy is the lord of hosts. And all the Earth is filled with his glory.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "So, you see, it's sometimes also di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So, you see, it's sometimes also difficult being a stick insect. The leg tried to move independently, making it hard to walk. But hearing about it makes you uncomfortable, I understand.

fields.Title: You: "I am a detective."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am a detective.

fields.Title: You: "I can't."
fields.Dialogue Text: I can't.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. I do not have a startle displa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. I do not have a startle display, so I use a neurodegenerative allomone to aid in camouflage. Do not worry, it is only destructive over long periods of time.

fields.Title: You: "Forget about it. It walked on water..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Forget about it. It walked on water!

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You're staring at me. For about thr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're staring at me. For about three minutes now.

fields.Title: You: "But I *want* to blink and undo 12 b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But I *want* to blink and undo 12 billion years of matter expansion.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "In the reeds, where he's pointing,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the reeds, where he's pointing, you see a flash of white -- *porcelain* white.

fields.Title: You: "(Yell.) "No!""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Yell.) "No!"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "You know who would know more -- a c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know who would know more -- a cryptozoologist!

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "This is the Insulindian..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "This is the Insulindian phasmid."
fields.Alternate1: (Whisper.) "That's the..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't think the pheromone will d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think the pheromone will do anything." His whisper turns to a sceptical hiss -- but he has stopped now.

fields.Title: You: "Retreat slowly. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Retreat slowly. [Leave.]

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The creature tilts its tiny head to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The creature tilts its tiny head to the side and appears to look at you. It is incredibly light, like the slightest gust of wind should blow it away, but it doesn't...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We can't just leave it standing th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We can't just leave it standing there. We have to do *something*, detective. It could be..." He thinks. "It could be connected somehow even..."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "...hissing and clicking, it extends..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...hissing and clicking, it extends its mandible-like antennae to greet you. You're right below it now, looking up at the colossal chitin of its white limbs. The head of the creature is crowned by reeds and its eyes are like small droplets of water.

fields.Title: You: ""Hello. I don't know who I am.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello. I don't know who I am."
fields.Alternate1: "Hello. I'm Harry. I don't really know who I am..."

fields.Title: You: "Disengage slowly. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Disengage slowly. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Raise the other hand too."
fields.Dialogue Text: Raise the other hand too.

fields.Title: You: ""Where did it go?" (Look north.) Ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where did it go?" (Look north.) Can *you* see it?"

fields.Title: You: ""How did it *do* that? Glide?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How did it *do* that? Glide?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "It's blending into the tufts of ree..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's blending into the tufts of reeds in the distance! Moving from islet to islet...

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "However hard you squint you can't m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: However hard you squint you can't make out anything recognizable, let alone a stick insect.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm not. We should have... it's my..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not. We should have... it's my fault too." He looks across the water. The slip of photo paper still drying in his hand, hanging despondently for a second.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "The segmented antennae move with ap..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The segmented antennae move with apprehension, searching for something that's not there...

fields.Title: The Deserter: "...and then he is back to staring a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...and then he is back to staring at the dust.

fields.Title: Logic: "The lieutenant had a *camera*. A ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant had a *camera*. A camera, he could have taken a picture. Now they'll all think you're mad...

fields.Title: Empathy: "The stimulus overloaded it. It's pa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The stimulus overloaded it. It's passing, like an extended moment, or a gall stone.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The sight of the insect pulses with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sight of the insect pulses with pain, as a streak of fire tries to shoot up your leg. You swallow it. Unmoved. Not now. There's blood dripping... warm.  The creature must feel it too, it twitches.

fields.Title: You: "I exist too."
fields.Dialogue Text: I exist too.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Tell me what it's like for you."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tell me what it's like for you.

fields.Title: You: "I'm glad to be me -- an incredibly..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm glad to be me -- an incredibly sensitive instrument.

fields.Title: You: "You don't have a foot there now!"
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't have a foot there now!

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "It would take a million years of ev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It would take a million years of evolution -- or a total reversal in the condition of the world -- for your pain to end.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No. There is *one* more."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. There is *one* more.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "She was hell on Earth. It doesn't t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was hell on Earth. It doesn't take a three-metre stick insect to tell you that.

fields.Title: You: ""What's that -- in the reeds?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's that -- in the reeds?"

fields.Title: You: "Have I always thought this way?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Have I always thought this way?

fields.Title: You: "No. There are no more thoughts."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. There are no more thoughts.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Cuno can't believe how bad he is, w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cuno can't believe how bad he is, without a camera -- in this situation the binoclard would be superior in every way.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah..." He shakes his head. "I do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah..." He shakes his head. "I don't have a camera. That sucks about Cuno."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Damn right, we just discovered a G..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn right, we just discovered a GIANT INSECT. Ain't no one done that..." He looks across the water.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""*Everyone*, yo! We gotta tell the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Everyone*, yo! We gotta tell the *world* about this. Case solved -- insect found. We're fuckin'... master detectives or some shit. We're *good*."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "You glance over your shoulder. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You glance over your shoulder. The lieutenant holds a piece of milled aluminium. He begins to pull it open, extremely carefully -- it's the camera!

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper) "Who cares what they *thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper) "Who cares what they *think* Kim."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Shh... okay." The lieutenant puts..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shh... okay." The lieutenant puts his finger to his lips and nods.

fields.Title: You: "Raise your hand slowly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Raise your hand slowly.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Suddenly there is silence."
fields.Dialogue Text: Suddenly there is silence.

fields.Title: You: "(Look behind you.) "It's smelling m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Look behind you.) "It's smelling me..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No." He shakes his head. "It's gon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No." He shakes his head. "It's gone for now, detective."
fields.Alternate1: "No." He shakes his head. "It's gone for now, lieutenant-yefreitor."
fields.Alternate2: "No." He shakes his head. "It's gone for now, Harry."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "And you, a detective of the RCM, st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And you, a detective of the RCM, standing there with your mouth agape -- alone and dumbfounded.

fields.Title: You: ""I think it went into the reeds the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it went into the reeds there, on that islet..." (Point North.)

fields.Title: You: ""What in the name of *god* was that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What in the name of *god* was that?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""*Like* you?" He shakes his head in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Like* you?" He shakes his head in disbelief. "I'm not an entomologist, okay -- neither was the para-scientist. Who knows, maybe you're right. The only thing I'm sure of is..."

fields.Title: You: ""Dammit. What now?" (Continue.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dammit. What now?" (Continue.)

fields.Title: You: ""We got it..." (Back off.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "We got it..." (Back off.)

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "A shudder pulses through the creatu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A shudder pulses through the creatures limbs. It jolts back to life, like a record continuing were it left off -- in a swaying, praying motion. Even the small black pearls of its eyes do not stray from you...

fields.Title: You: "I want to see inside you."
fields.Dialogue Text: I want to see inside you.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "As you back off the phasmid also ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you back off the phasmid also takes a step back into the reeds. Something tells you -- the next time you engage and disengage it will probably flee.

fields.Title: You: "I'm ill."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm ill.

fields.Title: You: "The fuck is happening to me right n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The fuck is happening to me right now?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "So am I. I was born to detect sucro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So am I. I was born to detect sucrose rewards and semiochemicals. What were you born to detect?

fields.Title: You: "It was very disorienting at first,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was very disorienting at first, but I'm keeping my shit together.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Thank you. I also have one final th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Thank you. I also have one final thing to say to you: that woman -- turn from the ruin. Turn and go *forward*.
fields.Alternate1: Thank you. I also have one more thing to say to you: that woman -- turn from the ruin. Turn and go forward. Do it for the working class.
fields.Alternate2: Thank you. I also have one more thing to say to you before you go. That woman -- turn from the ruin. Turn and go forward. For all mankind.
fields.Alternate3: Thank you. I also have one more thing to say to you before you go. That woman -- turn from the ruin. Turn and go forward. For Revachol.
fields.Alternate4: Thank you. I also have one more thing to say to you before you go. That woman -- turn from the ruin. Turn and go forward. For freedom.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I have stayed hidden through four f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I have stayed hidden through four forms of government and two scientific revolutions. Until I was accidentally discovered by a detective of the Citizens Militia in Revachol, district of Martinaise, March, '51.
fields.Alternate1: I have stayed hidden through four forms of government and two scientific revolutions. Three -- if you count stone tools. Until I was accidentally discovered by a detective of the Citizens Militia in Revachol, disctrict of Martinaise, March, '51.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "And the 4,000-year-old Seraseolitic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And the 4,000-year-old Seraseolitic civilization buried so deep in the sediment that you do not even know it is there -- they too did not see me.

fields.Title: You: "Too sensitive of a matter."
fields.Dialogue Text: Too sensitive of a matter.

fields.Title: You: "Was there an ancient Seraseolitic c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Was there an ancient Seraseolitic civilization?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "She was hell on Earth. It doesn't t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She was hell on Earth. It doesn't take a three-metre stick insect to tell you that.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Yes, it's light enough to do that...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, it's light enough to do that. Keep your eyes on the prize, it looks like material for some kind of nest there. You should search it.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Looks like someone's got hurt in a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like someone's got hurt in a fight. This antennae is much smaller than the other one.

fields.Title: Half Light: "It *definitely* had something to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It *definitely* had something to do with that! It was repelled by you, as if it was scared.

fields.Title: You: ""There was a pheromone -- like an o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There was a pheromone -- like an ox-spray. I had to have it on and I didn't."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""The fuck -- *pherone*? Man, this a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The fuck -- *pherone*? Man, this ain't about no phermone! This is about the *phasmid*. Did you *see* the size of that?!"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Take long, deep breaths. Slow down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Take long, deep breaths. Slow down your pulse. Don't move yet, and when you do -- be light as a feather.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "You glance over your shoulder. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You glance over your shoulder. The lieutenant holds a piece of milled aluminium. He begins to pull it open, extremely carefully...

fields.Title: You: "(Point to it.) "What is that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Point to it.) "What is that?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "With the sound of metal sliding aga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With the sound of metal sliding against metal, the lieutenant reveals the lens. The glass glints in his hand as he begins to slide in an ampoule...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "As you do, the invertebrate comes t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you do, the invertebrate comes to life, its limbs moving independent of each other. As if each has a mind of its own. They are white like stalks of porcelain, knitting above you.

fields.Title: Half Light: "No. Stop. Be afraid."
fields.Dialogue Text: No. Stop. Be afraid.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Perhaps it is preparing to *eat* it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Perhaps it is preparing to *eat* its god?

fields.Title: You: ""Did you get it, did you get the pi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you get it, did you get the picture?"

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, we should have helped the cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, we should have helped the cryptozoologists."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["tc.insulindian_phasmid"] == true  and  Variable["coast.morells_pheromone_spray"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.inspect_traps"] == false

fields.Title: You: ""We should have been more thorough..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should have been more thorough Kim. We should have..."

fields.Title: You: ""The cryptozoologist! There was one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The cryptozoologist! There was one in the bar. Maybe she knew something?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "You know who would know -- a crypto..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know who would know -- a cryptozoologist!

fields.Title: The Deserter: "Wordless, he's staring at the ash...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wordless, he's staring at the ash. Not responding to your yelling.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Immortalized."
fields.Dialogue Text: Immortalized.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The limb before you is incredibly l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The limb before you is incredibly light, like eggshell. It's much lighter than a reed. You feel a soft push could tip the creature over, its hollow exoskeleton collapsing...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. The leg tried to move around i..."
