fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. The leg tried to move around independently, making it hard to walk.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes, thankfully someone ate it. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, thankfully someone ate it. The next time I moulted I grew an antenna again!

fields.Title: You: "Way worse has happened to me."
fields.Dialogue Text: Way worse has happened to me.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It doesn't look like that, no.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It doesn't look like that, no."

fields.Title: You: "It's hell. I change my mind. I want..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's hell. I change my mind. I want to be you.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The pale, too, came with you. No on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The pale, too, came with you. No one remembers it before you. The cnidarians do not, the radially symmetricals do not. There is an almost unanimous agreement between the birds and the plants that you are going to destroy us all.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, the pale is human made?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, the pale is human made?

fields.Title: You: ""You didn't get the picture?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You didn't get the picture?"

fields.Title: You: "What *is* that?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What *is* that?

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno, do you have a camera or some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno, do you have a camera or something?"

fields.Title: You: "Approach carefully."
fields.Dialogue Text: Approach carefully.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You cannot lie to me. Behind you it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You cannot lie to me. Behind you it smells of fires. So awfully far you were prepared to go in her presence. End it.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He cannot believe what he's saying..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He cannot believe what he's saying too much.

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What now..." the old man behind yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now..." the old man behind you repeats suddenly. He's put his hand into the ash -- it's dirty and black.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Our suspect is not looking so good..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our suspect is not looking so good. We need to check on him."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Look! In the reeds, where the phasm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look! In the reeds, where the phasmid was hiding -- you see a little flash of white -- porcelain white. In a nest of some sort?

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, yeah right there -- it doesn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, yeah right there -- it doesn't like bein' out in the open. Shifty fuck. It's gone now, but..." He pants. "Wow."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, cryptologist, exactly! Those..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, cryptologist, exactly! Those are the fucks who study them. This is *unreal*, man..." He runs out of breath.

fields.Title: You: ""The cryptozoologist! There was one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The cryptozoologist! There was one in the bar. Maybe she knew something?"

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "The hiss is different from the stri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The hiss is different from the strings you heard before. It says something *else*, in a lower pitch...

fields.Title: You: "(Say something to the insect, quiet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Say something to the insect, quietly, like...)
fields.Alternate1: (Say something to it, quietly... something like...)

fields.Title: Empathy: "It moves just an inch closer to you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It moves just an inch closer to you. Or does it only *feel* like it does?

fields.Title: Empathy: "You've never seen him get this exci..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've never seen him get this excited. His voice is almost trembling.

fields.Title: You: "Back off."
fields.Dialogue Text: Back off.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""In three," the lieutenant whispers..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In three," the lieutenant whispers, his voice is tense. "If it moves, you jump back, I'll shoot. Here we go. Three, two, one..."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "There is uncertainty in his phrasin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is uncertainty in his phrasing.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Am I?" He shakes his head. "I don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Am I?" He shakes his head. "I don't know. I'm not an entomologist! Neither was the para-scientist. The only thing I'm sure of is..."

fields.Title: You: ""The cryptozoologist... there was o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The cryptozoologist... there was one in the bar. I bet she knew something..."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "The sensation is electrifying, reso..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sensation is electrifying, resounding through your body.

fields.Title: You: "Pull your hand away."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pull your hand away.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Don't say it! Are you sure? This ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't say it! Are you sure? This may be the only chance you get to touch it...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Then I will tell you what it's like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then I will tell you what it's like for me.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Are you sure?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Are you sure?

fields.Title: You: "A small leg. That's horrible."
fields.Dialogue Text: A small leg. That's horrible.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Few of us can begin to imagine the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Few of us can begin to imagine the horror of you -- with all of creation reflected in your forebrain. It must be like the highest of hells, a kaleidoscope of fire and writhing glass. Eternal damnation.

fields.Title: You: "You're destroying him?"
fields.Dialogue Text: You're destroying him?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes -- with stone tools and silk. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes -- with stone tools and silk. They too missed me, although I had not developed the mutation needed for parthenogenesis yet, and scoured the neolithic hinterland as distinct individuals, not clones.

fields.Title: You: ""No. I told you what it's about. Ou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I told you what it's about. Our fate."

fields.Title: You: ""It can walk on water?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It can walk on water?"

fields.Title: You: "I will be extra extra careful not t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I will be extra extra careful not to blink, stick insect. Don't worry.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "A series of chirrups surrounds you,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A series of chirrups surrounds you, like swallows on a cliff side, as the phasmid moves its forearms -- tymbals visible on the inside of its white stalks...

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Relax. Now that you *know* it's her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Relax. Now that you *know* it's here -- how long can it hide?

fields.Title: You: ""Where did it go?" (Look North.) Ca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where did it go?" (Look North.) Can *you* see it?"

fields.Title: You: ""How did it *do* that? Glide?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How did it *do* that? Glide?"

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Tik-tik-tik... hisss... tik-tik-tik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tik-tik-tik... hisss... tik-tik-tik... hisss....

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is," the lieutenant whispers be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is," the lieutenant whispers behind you. You hear the familiar ring of his jacket unzipping -- slowly. Painstakingly so...

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper) "Are you sure you won't s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper) "Are you sure you won't scare it off?"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "No! The sound of the flash will sca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No! The sound of the flash will scare the creature off. Warn him NOW!

fields.Title: Composure: "Something in its body language has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something in its body language has changed, just slightly...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Slowly, with your breath held, you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Slowly, with your breath held, you take two small steps toward the phasmid. The creature lets out a series of ultrasonic clicks that swarm around your head like swallows...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The insect stops its stridulation,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The insect stops its stridulation, seeming to observe you. Below its crown of reeds, little pin-prick eyes detect motion, glittering. The world stands still around you.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Apricot blossoms. White blossoms er..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Apricot blossoms. White blossoms erupting. A sensation, like cold hands on your face.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Insulindian Phasmid: "The invertebrate stops, raising its..."]
Kim Kitsuragi: ""Maybe it *is* real, the pheromone...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe it *is* real, the pheromone..." The lieutenant's mouth is agape.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The insect's head is crowned with r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The insect's head is crowned with reed-like scales, the shape of seed heads. They rustle as the air moves. The ventricles at its abdomen continue to expanding, like lunglets...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay, but..." He shakes his head i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but..." He shakes his head in disbelief. "I'm not an entomologist, okay? Neither was the para-scientist. Who knows? The only thing I'm sure of is..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He shakes his head. In silence -- a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He shakes his head. In silence -- an expression on his face that you've never seen there before.

fields.Title: You: ""Tell me you got the picture...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tell me you got the picture..."

fields.Title: The Deserter: ""What are you talking about, *phero..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you talking about, *pheromone*?" The strange state the old man is in ends, momentarily. Something in the word animates him...

fields.Title: The Deserter: "Your voice echoes alone on the wate..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your voice echoes alone on the water. Not so much as a scoff from the old man.

fields.Title: You: "*Slowly* reach out and touch the cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Slowly* reach out and touch the creature's whisker.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Be careful, detective... It's movi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Be careful, detective... It's moving."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "It tastes like... sugar. Very faint..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It tastes like... sugar. Very faint. The arthropod towers above you, tufts of reeds pointing from limb and head alike.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The arthropod towers above you -- j..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The arthropod towers above you -- just like in the picture -- oblivious to your chattering. The ventricles on its abdomen slowly expanding, vestigial wings like barely visible gossamer hanging from the inside of its slender joints.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Nothing. Its simple eyes give off n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing. Its simple eyes give off no flicker of light, no one is home. The twitches of its limbs are insect-like, unknowable, perhaps without substance even.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim... there's something there.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim... there's something there."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I do not have fire inside me. In me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I do not have fire inside me. In me there is not even blood, but lymph -- like sap from a wine palm.

fields.Title: You: ""What does it look like?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What does it look like?"

fields.Title: You: "We need to know. Perhaps it's sent..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We need to know. Perhaps it's sent to us by a god?

fields.Title: You: ""Sort of.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sort of."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He squints. "Looks like a nest of s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He squints. "Looks like a nest of some sort? We should have a look."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. I once cloned myself and ate t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. I once cloned myself and ate the little ones. It was winter and I woke up at the wrong time. It was an accident.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Simian butcherer... Soon, one of yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Simian butcherer... Soon, one of you will close your eyes -- and open them to see that none of this ever existed.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Cuno can't believe how lame he is -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cuno can't believe how lame he is -- without the camera right now. Should have stolen one, a real cop would have one...

fields.Title: Cuno: ""A nest?" The whisper is anxious. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A nest?" The whisper is anxious. "We can't get to it yet, don't scare it off. Maybe later..."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "In the reeds, where the phasmid was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the reeds, where the phasmid was hiding, you see a little flash of white -- porcelain white.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yo, our suspect's not looking so g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yo, our suspect's not looking so good. We need to check on him -- also," he points to the reeds.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Our suspect's not looking so good...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our suspect's not looking so good. We need to check on him -- also, man..." he points to the reeds.

fields.Title: You: "Listen carefully..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Listen carefully...

fields.Title: You: ""Kim..." (Whisper.) "The flash is l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim..." (Whisper.) "The flash is loud. It won't like that."
fields.Alternate1: (Whisper.) "It sounds like a weapon, Kim. It won't like that."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "The spindly mechanism turns itself..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The spindly mechanism turns itself back to you, its antennae taking their measure of the air, slowly...

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper.) "What is that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper.) "What is that?"

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "You see the insect turn to him, its..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see the insect turn to him, its mandible antennae reaching out. Its motions are quick, sudden.
fields.Alternate1: You see the phasmid turn to him, its mandible antennae reaching out. The motions are quick, sudden.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I have absolutely no idea..." The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have absolutely no idea..." The lieutenant whispers back. You hear the familiar ring of his jacket unzipping -- slowly. Painstakingly so...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't think..." He tries to expl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think..." He tries to explain, patting slightly: "I don't think it had *anything* to do with the ox-spray. It was just scared."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't understand... I *had* the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't understand... I *had* the pheromone...."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing, swallow it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing, swallow it.

fields.Title: Volition: "He subdues the feeling. Dusts himse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He subdues the feeling. Dusts himself off and moves on. So should you. There will be other chances.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cryptozoologist? Oh god, there was one...

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "We missed it, he thinks. We damn mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: We missed it, he thinks. We damn missed a spot. We should have... then the lieutenant collects himself.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't understand... I *had* the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't understand... I *had* the pheromone...."

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "I am at the end of a narrow funnel...."
fields.Dialogue Text: I am at the end of a narrow funnel. Weightless. So light it only feels like *something* to be me. In truth -- perhaps I'm nothing? I certainly do not have a soul. And if I did, it would never ache.
fields.Alternate1: I am at the end of a narrow funnel. Weightless. So light it only feels like *something* to be me. In truth -- perhaps I'm nothing? I certainly do not have a soul. And if I did, it would never burn.

fields.Title: You: "Okay. I don't want to hear more abo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay. I don't want to hear more about that.

fields.Title: You: "Are you the miracle?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Are you the miracle?

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes. No one detected me for such a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. No one detected me for such a long, long time. For thousands of years. I dithered, out of sight. Draped myself in greenery.

fields.Title: You: "What exactly *are* you?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What exactly *are* you?

fields.Title: You: ""What now?" [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now?" [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Apparently, yes -- like a water st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apparently, yes -- like a water strider, only..." He shakes his head with amazement. "I've never seen *anything* like that in my life."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We are now just another pair of cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We are now just another pair of crackpots who did not take a picture of the giant cryptid.... Maybe we'll get another chance? We *know* it's here now..."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cool. So's Cuno -- Cuno's also hav..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool. So's Cuno -- Cuno's also having a vision of a *giant insect*. And it's *real*. Back off before it eats you..."

fields.Title: You: ""Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it right..." [Leave in rage.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Someone must have known about it t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone must have known about it though. Maybe there's some secret to approaching it? I have no idea... I've never heard of a species like that."

fields.Title: You: "Of all the creatures I've met you a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of all the creatures I've met you are the most beautiful.

fields.Title: You: "What woman?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What woman?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It looks like the insect had some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It looks like the insect had some kind of nest there, look... Maybe it has left *some* proof..."

fields.Title: You: ""Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it! Damn it! I didn't get it right..." [Leave in rage.]

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, we should have helped the cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, we should have helped the cryptozoologists."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Three-hundred metres inland special..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Three-hundred metres inland special consultant Trant Heidelstam cups his ear. Satellite-Officer Vicquemare nods to him on the jetty: "I heard it."

fields.Title: You: ""What now?" (Continue.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "What now?" (Continue.)

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, it walked on water, like a w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, it walked on water, like a water spider, or like -- one of those water walkers..." He's lost for words, just pants from excitement. "This cop-shit is *insane*."

fields.Title: You: "(Whisper) "I have the pheromone, I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Whisper) "I have the pheromone, I can approach it."

fields.Title: Endurance: "Sweat drips from your brow, soaking..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sweat drips from your brow, soaking your chest... you reek of it, your chemicals.

fields.Title: You: "Stand on your tiptoes and look more..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stand on your tiptoes and look more closely...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Careful. It may be poisonous." The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Careful. It may be poisonous." The lieutenant watches you apprehensively.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Sets of complex eyes follow you --d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sets of complex eyes follow you --droplets of dew on either side of the head.

fields.Title: You: ""We could have learned something ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We could have learned something about the phasmid's behaviour. Searched for it with them."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Crypto-*fascist* probably."
fields.Dialogue Text: Crypto-*fascist* probably.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I got it..." You hear the lieutena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I got it..." You hear the lieutenant whisper, as the creature's shape develops onto photo paper in his hand: a polychrome ghost of white streaks against the reeds and the sky. And you, as a shadow before it.

fields.Title: You: "Look at your finger."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at your finger.

fields.Title: You: "Run your hand up the slender limb,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Run your hand up the slender limb, higher...

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "There is no mind to speak of. And i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is no mind to speak of. And if there is, it's beyond your imagination -- too simple to be compatible with yours. Segmented mouthparts foam, it tilts its head.

fields.Title: You: "Where does this come from? All this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Where does this come from? All this? Around us? The world?

fields.Title: You: "If I tell you, what will happen?"
fields.Dialogue Text: If I tell you, what will happen?

fields.Title: You: "On the horizon. Pale fire. This thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: On the horizon. Pale fire. This thing we're both sensing is coming to an end.

fields.Title: You: "That's cool."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's cool.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "So what if the next picture doesn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So what if the next picture doesn't come? This creature is not the photographer, just the camera.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes, I am lucky. It is nothing comp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, I am lucky. It is nothing compared to the horror that is you -- with all of creation reflected in your forebrain. A nerve mirror of horrifying fidelity. Constant, never-ending damnation.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Even when you're sleeping... And wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even when you're sleeping... And when you wake, you carry it around on your neck. With eyes open that cannot help but swallow more behind the mirror. I feel great, mute empathy for you.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "Yes, compared to the immeasurable,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, compared to the immeasurable, fiery empyrean of glass and terror in *your* head, it seems trivial. I just thought you should know.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "That must be incredibly hard. The a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That must be incredibly hard. The arthropods are in silent and meaningless awe of you. Know that we are watching -- when you're tired, when the vision spins out of control. The insects will be looking on. Rooting for you.

fields.Title: Volition: "In honour of your shit, lieutenant-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In honour of your shit, lieutenant-yefreitor. Which you kept *together* in the face of total, unrelenting terror. Day after day. Second by second.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "DETECTIVE"
fields.Dialogue Text: DETECTIVE

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Yes, of course. The three metres ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, of course. The three metres tall stick insect would be offended.
fields.Alternate1: Yes, of course. The three metres tall stick insect would be *offended*.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Instead of air, you exhale thoughts..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Instead of air, you exhale thoughts. There are no trees that eat thoughts.

fields.Title: Insulindian Phasmid: "No -- you're only thinking it *now*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No -- you're only thinking it *now*. This is a revelation.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah -- real normal. There's a gia..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah -- real normal. There's a giant stick insect there. Back off, before it eats you..."

fields.Title: You: "Of all the creatures I've met you a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of all the creatures I've met you are the kindest.

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing. Just looking at the stick..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing. Just looking at the stick insect. Everything is normal."
